  "text": "tion (\"repriming\") to be from 5 to 40 sec [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . To test whether the delay period from endocytosis to exocytosis was increased in stoned mutants, we examined the lapsed time required before loaded dye could be released from NMJ boutons. FM1-43 dye was loaded with high-K ϩ saline (30 sec and 1 and 5 min), and then the preparation was washed in calcium-free saline for a variable period (⌬t ϭ 0 and 30 sec and 1, 5, 10, and 15 min) before K ϩ -evoked unloading (⌬t ϭ 0 and 30 sec and 1 and 5 min). No significant change between controls and stoned mutant boutons in the amounts of FM1-43 release was detected in these assays (data not shown). These studies suggest that although fewer SVs are recycled via the endo-exo pool in stoned mutants, no difference in the rate of SV maturation was detectable.",
